STEVENS v. WARDEN OF THE MARYLAND PENITENTIARY [App. No. 81,

September Term, 1964.]

Decided December 7, 1964.

Before Henderson, C. J., and Hammond, Prescott, Horney, Marbury, Sybert and Oppenheimer, JJ.

PER Curiam.

Application for leave to appeal from a denial of post conviction relief is denied for the reasons set out in the opinion of Judge Foster in the court below.

Application denied.
